other_tests.findings: A 1.4 x 1.4 cm T2 hyperintense lesion is consistent with a cyst or biliary hamartoma. Mild hydronephrosis of the right kidney secondary to compression of the ureter. A mildly dilated, straightened appendix measuring 7.7 mm is seen with mild wall thickening. No periappendiceal fat stranding and the remaining bowel is normal.
